cs.ET, cs.AR, cs.DC, cs.PL, cs.LO

Reasoning: 
- cs.ET (Emerging Technologies): The paper discusses the emerging technology of reversible logic and proposes a novel concept of partial reversible gates. 
- cs.AR (Architecture): The paper proposes a new architecture for designing reversible BCD arithmetic circuits using partial reversible gates. 
- cs.DC (Digital Circuits): The paper deals with the design of digital circuits for BCD arithmetic using reversible logic. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages): Although not directly related to programming languages, the paper proposes a new concept in logic design which could potentially have implications in programming language design. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science): The paper deals with the design of logic circuits using reversible logic and proposes a new concept of partial reversible gates.
